        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 25 at 6:05PM MDT until July 25 at 6:45PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 605 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 25 miles west of
Baker, moving southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Trained spotters reported quarter sized hail 2 miles
north of Ismay, MT.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Baker, Plevna, Ismay, Westmore, Willard, Ollie and Knowlton.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds and has
produced large hail.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
